        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 4:55PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking showers and thunderstorms
with gusty winds moving towards the Gallatin Valley.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bozeman, Belgrade, Manhattan, Maudlow, Four Corners, Amsterdam,
Bozeman Hot Springs, Church Hill, Gallatin Gateway, and Menard.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
